50|$|The {{relationship}} of the Japonic (or Japanese-Ryukyuan) languages to other languages and language families is controversial. There are numerous hypotheses, none of which is generally accepted. Japonic is classified as an <b>isolated</b> <b>language</b> family and shows in its proto-form strong similarities to Southeast Asian languages.|$|R
