5000|$|The {{languages}} are: {{the great}} linguistic family Chibchan, of probable Central American origin; the great South American families Arawakan, Cariban, Quechuan and Tupian; seven families only {{present at the}} regional level (Chocó, Guahibo, Saliba, Macu, Witoto, Bora, Tucano). The ten <b>isolated</b> <b>languages</b> are: Andoque, Awa-cuaiquer, Cofán, Guambiano, Kamentsá, Páez, Ticuna, Tinigua, Yagua, Yaruro.|$|R
